In just a few months, Deadpool 3, one of most anticipated comic book movies of all time, will reunite the live-action Deadpool and Wolverine for the first time in 15 years. We've come a long way since X-Men Origins: Wolverine, so we thought it would be cool to go back and check out another meeting between Logan and Wade in 2009 via Hulk Vs Wolverine. Produced when the MCU was a gleam in Kevin Feige's eye, it shows a more comic book accurate Marvel Universe, but does the film stand the test of time? All that plus Hulk vs Thor Odinson as a bonus in this action-packed episode of the Major Issues Podcast. **Get 1 month FREE of Magic Mind, when you’re subscribing for 3 months at:** [**https://www.magicmind.com/JANmajorissues**](https://www.magicmind.com/JANmajorissues) **with my code: MAJORISSUES20 It’s an extra 20% off! This only lasts until the end of January, so hurry up before it goes away.**

